Class BasicDoubleLinkedList<T>

java.lang.Object
BasicDoubleLinkedList<T>
Type Parameters:
T -
Direct Known Subclasses:
SortedDoubleLinkedList
public class BasicDoubleLinkedList<T> extends Object
This generic double-linked implements the Javaâ€™s Iterable interface and relies on a head and tail. Both the head and the tail are set to null when the list is empty. Both point to the same element when there is only one element in the list. A node structure has three fields: data, next and the previous references.
Author:
Yei Thek Wang

    • remove

      public BasicDoubleLinkedList<T> remove​(T targetData, Comparator<T> comparator)
      This method cycles through every node on the list until it finds a match, then cuts that node out of the list. If it doesn't find a match, it doesn't change anything.
      Parameters:
      targetData - The data to be matched and then removed
      comparator - The comparator used to check whether the data is a match
      Returns:
      BasicDoubleLinkedList A reference to the list, either changed, unchanged, or empty
